## 2. Competitive Landscape

| Competitor | Model | Strengths | Weaknesses |
|-----------|-------|-----------|-----------|
| **Ownwell** ($50M Series B) | Full-service, contingency fee (25-35%) | 1M+ appeals, 86% win rate, nationwide | Opaque AI, no user transparency on *how* reduction is found |
| **PropertyTax.io** | Full-service, evidence portal | End-to-end management, hearing attendance | Black-box analysis â€” homeowner has zero visibility |
| **Texas Tax Protest** | Full-service, big data | 10+ years in TX market | Legacy tech, no vision/condition analysis |
| **ProtestPro** | Launching May 2026 | New entrant, Collin County focus | Unproven |
| **Rainbolt & Co** | Service firm + proprietary platform | Trained on resolved hearings data | Houston-only, service model only |
| **Smart Appeal AI** | DIY report generator | Low cost | Shallow analysis, no local data depth |
| **AppealEdge** | Comp finder | Quick comparable search | No evidence packet, no AI condition analysis |

### Where We Already Win

